{"key":"processedPost-6718628","value":{"id":6718628,"first":6717912,"last":6718637,"when":1175059314,"utime":"03/28/07 08:21 AM","content":"There should be zero standing water in the perlite.  Standing water makes the perlite below the waterline useless.  Three to five inches of well drained perlite will maintain humidity for over a month.  In addition, there should be drain holes in the floor of the terrarium.  Misting the cakes adds plenty of moisture to the perlite.  Even if the perlite on the very top dries, what is below doesn't.<br />Remove, rinse well, and drain between crop cycles and you can use the same perlite for years.<br />RR","title":"Re: Moistening perlite"}}